column2: The example below describes the brake module and several servodrives, which are linked via AX-Bridge modules to make up a drivesystem. We recommend that the brake module be placed in thefirst position with the AX-Bridge power supply module (AX5901)and after that the servo drives with decreasing rated current; weassume here that the most powerful servo drive also releases thegreatest brake energy.CAUTION!Uncontrolled movements!If the drive system is disconnected from the mains due to a mainsfailure, all axes of the drive system make uncontrolled movements.Take suitable measures to ensure than no persons are endan-gered during this time. Vertical axes are particularly dangerous.
